data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
v1.84 * Fix system name not updating from log files * Update elite.json and station.csv
v1.83 * Don't flatline one CPU core scanning log files (sorry 'bout that...)
v1.82 * Fix Crash on Startup (if you had a log file line longer than 1000 characters)
v1.81 * Add EDDN message counting by app and version * EditOcrResults window fixes * Fix No way to clear ORC corrections if you don't want to import #14 * Add EDDN Spool to File * Fix Can't cancel the "load a calibration screenshot" window #41 * Fix Manual calibration doesn't let you set the 12th point correctly, according to user feedback. #39 * Fix Item duplication in the Edit Results window #13
v1.8 * Add MRmP's editable calibration system * Add magnifier for calibration purposes * Remove incredibly-dumb bug that has been eating the spaces in station names... d'oh... * Check for empty string from EDDN, and at least don't crash on general malformed data
v1.73 * Update Station.csv and Elite.json. * Swap the Levenshtein algorithm for one that works (!) and tweak parameters it compares to * Fix button on station-to-station tab
v1.72 * Include MRmP's (experimental) automatic calibration. Please feed back to the forum or GitHub if this works well - or not - for your resolution. Likely will not work at all if you have changed your FOV settings. * Crashes now generate a RegulatedNoiseDump.dmp file. Passing this to the developers is INCREDIBLY helpful in fixing the problems. * Fix auto-import checkbox not set on load * capture some game settings e.g. resolution * fix automatic directory detection on 32-bit * fix can't start without DisplaySettings.xml
v1.71 * Fix RegulatedNoise crash on Elite Dangerous startup * Fix version history
v1.7 * station-to-station overhauled: now shows all round trips in a big list, can work in credits-per-light-year, shows outbound and return at the same time * Merge MRmP's changes to product directory detection * Move elite.json and station.csv to a Data subfolder * Check at startup for a new version, and notify the user if one is found * Fix GitHub issue #3: update station-to-station when updating rest of GUI * Don't crash when calculating distances to systems that we don't know the location of * fix rename-loses-source-of-data bug
v1.6 * Add new OCR Corrections form ("Edit" button on Corrections tab)
v1.5 * add Maddavo's stations data (static copy) to auto-fix station name OCR errors (thanks to Maddavo) - this also gives us pad-size information, but not using that yet * Move a bunch of code to make Form1.cs a less-depressing place to be * Add an auto-import checkbox and setting - this defaults to Off at the moment * Add Purge All EDDN Data function * Remove improbable punctuation from station names (but not apostrophes...) * Data imported from EDDN now has "<From EDDN>" as the "Screenshot Name" * He Suits is now H.E. Suits... also added Resonating Separators to the hard-coded list of commodity names
v1.41 * Fix Transaction credits does not accept numbers >100 (GitHub issue #1)
v1.4 * Add "within x light years of arbitrary system" * Add buttons linking to system maps and routes at http://starchart.club - with thanks to Biteketkergetek * Goosem@n's fix
v1.33 * Fix station name needs a space when you rename it error * Throw away exceptions when cloning main captured-screenshot bitmap for display purposes LOL * Create Brainerous images directory if it doesn't exist
v1.32 * Another bug fix via iAmLegion, hopefully fixes a lot of crash-during-OCR problems
v1.31 * Use ImaginaryEd's improved commodity-name-matching algorithm
v1.3 * Optionally recolour the UI - it's not great but it's as good as it's going to get for the time being :-) * [iAmLegion] fix import of system data when locale doesn't use "." as decimal separator
v1.2 * Add ability to restrict price analysis to systems within x light years, based on * Add ability to handle different UI colours than orange - hit the big obvious button on the Calibration tab to find out more * Also, no need to restart app if it finds no rows - it will pop a message to warn you, but will then try again with the next screenshot. Popup might need removing in due course because it steals focus and that's evil...
v1.12 * Increase speed at which EDDN import can run * Improve handling when Frontier products directory isn't set correctly
v1.11 * Default to the EDDN test schema for exports (imports currently run on both the live and test schemas) * Don't export to EDDN if the system name is undetected (i.e. "SomeSystem")
v1.1 * Edit and delete data on the Commodity and Station tabs of Price Analysis * Sort grids by clicking column headers in webpages * Extra navigation links in the trade data webpage * Add maximum-round-trip and find-best-round-trip to Station-to-Station tab of Price Analysis * Handle "can't find any rows of data in your screenshots" situation gracefully rather than crashing * [surtex] tweak exception handler for Crop() which might help us debug it * [steelyeyed] fix up OCR help a bit to match recent changes * [jippyuk] add delete-screenshot-after-import checkbox * [various] make the commodity-matching algorithm a bit more tolerant - please report any occasions when it mis-matches a commodity name * [snake man] remove "categoryName" from EDDN export
v1.0 * Rename to RegulatedNoise. Your old settings file and calibration file are NOT valid, but commodity CSVs (including auto-saves) and Commander's Logs can be copied from EliteOCRReader installs. * Add EliteBrainerous OCR for number recognition - vast improvement in number OCR (still uses Tesseract for letters) * Auto-import each screenshot as it completes * Add better queueing to OCR * Persist username and other OCR settings * Add swap-stations button to Station-To-Station tab (thanks to jippyuk for the idea) * Add logging code * You can now rename stations as well as systems. You can use this to merge two stations where one has the wrong name, too.
v0.93 * Fix OCR second-screenshot crash found by "Snake Man" * More tiny OCR logic tweaks * Fixed rare bug where a "\r" character in the CSV output caused a crash on import
v0.92: * Report exceptions to the screen to assist with debugging. Note that popup windows telling you the app has crashed may appear *behind* the main window, which is particularly unhelpful. * Possible fix for RegulatedNoise continuing to run in the background when you've already closed it.
v0.91: * Options to start Webserver and OCR on load - now you can just start the app and play. * OCR-on-load uses the last directory you manually selected for OCR * Webserver settings now preserved: network interface and colour scheme * Reset your settings, if you need to, by deleting RegulatedNoiseSettings.XML in the app directory
v0.9: * Correct multiple screenshots in one go - just take more than one shot. Works with web or GUI. Don't use this to capture prices from more than one *station* in one go, it will mangle the station names etc.! * Restructure tabs to make app less-baffling to newcomers * From now on, capturing OCR data gives you a link back to the original screenshot, so you can verify data days later. Go to the Station tab and double-click in the last column * Various specific OCR tweaks, like "ignore ENTER HANGAR" * Bits and pieces like a "Clear" button in the webserver OCR correction field, also webserver numeric fields are now labelled as such, so your phone/tablet will give you the right keyboard for edit
v0.8.1:
* Handle failure to find Frontier directories gracefully * Add Help and Changelog tab * Add startup debugging - hold LEFT-SHIFT before you start the app
v0.8:
* Now reads system names from your netLog files (and will offer to configure appConfig.xml for you too); uses those names to set OCR field and also to create Commander's Log events (automatic system history!); * Commander's Log actually usable now (web interface currently b0rked for Commander's Log though); * Commodities and Commander's Log autosaved and autoloaded on exit and start; * EDDN Export now defaults to Off
